&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Trekking in the rocky mountains of Cat Ba &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;carries many risks due to the sharp, steep, and extremely slippery limestone (karst) terrain when humidity is high. To ensure safety, visitors must equip themselves with hiking shoes that have specialized grip, use protective gloves to avoid having the cat&#039;s-ear rocks cut their hands, and absolutely never split off from the group on their own in the dense forest areas of the National Park.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:17pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Why does the rocky terrain of Cat Ba carry so many danger warnings?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Jade Island Cat Ba is famous not only for its poetic beaches but is also a paradise for adventure enthusiasts. However, behind that majestic beauty lie &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;danger warnings&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; that everyone needs to keep in mind. The terrain here is mainly long-weathered limestone, forming cat&#039;s-ear rock outcrops as sharp as razor blades.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Clearly understanding the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;things to note when trekking in the rocky mountain areas of Cat Ba&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; is a prerequisite before you set foot here. Unlike the earthen mountains in the northern highland provinces, Cat Ba&#039;s limestone is very hard but easily chipped, creating sharp edges that can tear shoes and clothing and cause deep injuries if you accidentally slip. In particular, the humidity blowing in from the sea combined with the dense forest canopy keeps the rock surfaces constantly damp and moss-covered, creating unpredictable slippery &quot;traps&quot;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/uploads/0000/1/2025/12/30/canh-bao-nguy-hiem-nhung-luu-y-khi-trekking-vao-khu-vuc-nui-da-cat-ba-7.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;900&quot; height=&quot;675&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:17pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Things to note when trekking in the rocky mountain areas of Cat Ba regarding equipment preparation&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;A safe trip begins with preparing your equipment properly. Never underestimate the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;danger warnings&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; from those who went before about using flimsy gear.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Hiking shoes - The most important shield&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Shoes are the most important item in the list of &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;things to note when trekking in the rocky mountain areas of Cat Ba&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;. You should not use ordinary running shoes or flat-soled canvas shoes.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Sole: Must have deep lugs, made of load-bearing rubber (such as Vibram soles) to increase the contact area and grip on smooth limestone.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Shoe collar: Choose a high or mid-cut design to protect your ankle from rolling (sprains) when moving over rough terrain.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Water resistance: Should have a waterproof membrane while still being breathable so your feet do not feel stuffy in the tropical environment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3 dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Protective gloves and specialized clothing&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;When moving across rocky mountains, having to use your hands to grip the cliff face is unavoidable. One of the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;things to note when trekking in the rocky mountain areas of Cat Ba&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; that few people pay attention to is the pair of gloves.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Gloves: Choose ones with rubber or suede palms to protect your hands from the razor-sharp rock edges.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Clothing: Use quick-drying, highly durable fabric to avoid tearing when rubbing against thorny plants or cat&#039;s-ear rocks. Long pants are a mandatory choice to avoid insects and scratches.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/uploads/0000/1/2025/12/30/canh-bao-nguy-hiem-nhung-luu-y-khi-trekking-vao-khu-vuc-nui-da-cat-ba-5.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;900&quot; height=&quot;582&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:17pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Danger warnings: How to recognize risks from nature?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Cat Ba&#039;s nature is very abundant but also full of risks if you lack experience. Reading and understanding the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;danger warnings&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; from the surrounding environment will help you make the right decisions.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Sudden weather changes: Unexpected downpours can turn a dry path into a deadly &quot;slide&quot; in just a few minutes. If it rains, the most important thing to note when trekking in the rocky mountain areas of Cat Ba is to find a safe shelter and stop climbing immediately.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Wildlife: Cat Ba is home to many species of venomous snakes and insects. Entering dark rock crevices or bushes without observing carefully is reckless.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Disorientation: The undulating limestone mountain system looks very similar, making it easy to lose your way without GPS or a local guide.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:13pt;color:#e74c3c;background-color:#ffffff;vertical-align:baseline;&quot;&gt;In addition, discover many more high-quality travel experiences at&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://vietnamtoure.com/&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:13pt;color:#e74c3c;background-color:#ffffff;vertical-align:baseline;&quot;&gt; Vietnamtoure.com&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/uploads/0000/1/2025/12/30/canh-bao-nguy-hiem-nhung-luu-y-khi-trekking-vao-khu-vuc-nui-da-cat-ba-4.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;900&quot; height=&quot;600&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:17pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Things to note when trekking in the rocky mountain areas of Cat Ba to maintain good fitness&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Rocky mountain trekking burns twice as much energy as walking on flat ground. To avoid the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;danger warnings&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; related to exhaustion or heat stroke, you need a sensible strategy for distributing your energy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Hydration and electrolyte strategy&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;In Cat Ba&#039;s dense forest, humidity is regularly above 80%, causing the body to sweat continuously without the sweat evaporating, leading to rapid dehydration.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Drink small sips of water every 15 minutes; do not wait until you are thirsty to drink.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Use effervescent electrolyte tablets to replenish the mineral salts lost through sweat. This is an extremely important &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;thing to note when trekking in the rocky mountain areas of Cat Ba&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; to avoid cramping in the middle of a cliff.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3 dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:14pt;margin-bottom:4pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:13pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Breathing control technique&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;When facing steep rock slopes, maintain a steady breathing rhythm in time with your steps. Do not try to climb too fast and run out of breath. If you feel your heart beating excessively fast, stop and rest in a spot with stable footing. Losing control of your breathing is the first &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;danger warning&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; that your body is overloaded.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;/uploads/0000/1/2025/12/30/canh-bao-nguy-hiem-nhung-luu-y-khi-trekking-vao-khu-vuc-nui-da-cat-ba-3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;900&quot; height=&quot;631&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:18pt;margin-bottom:4pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:17pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;How to move safely on karst limestone terrain?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Movement technique is a vital factor that helps you properly follow the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:bold;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;things to note when trekking in the rocky mountain areas of Cat Ba&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;. Apply the following rules:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The three-point contact rule: When climbing, always ensure at least three solid points of contact (two hands and one foot, or two feet and one hand) on the rock.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li dir=&quot;ltr&quot; style=&quot;line-height:1.38;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:11pt;font-family:Arial, sans-serif;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;Check the rock&#039;s stability: Limestone may look solid but can be crumbly or come loose. Lightly tap it with the tip of your foot or hand before placing your full body weight on it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
